<HEAD>Neat-o! Bush Poses For Photo With Denver Football Players</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS last graf with score, 14-10 Denver</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush told a elementary school class
Monday that some of the ``fun stuff'' he gets to do for being
leader of the free world includes getting his picture snapped with
famous football players.
   On this occasion, the location was Washington. The team was
Denver. The famous player was Broncos quarterback John Elway.
   Later, in a meeting with fifth graders at Pickard Elementary
School in Chicago, Bush was asked how he liked being president.
   ``You know what I got to do? Some of the boys are going to be
interested. Just before I came here, I got to meet the quarterback
for the Denver Broncos Football Team and I know Mike Ditka (Chicago
Bears coach) ... so I get some fun stuff to do in sports.''
   Also attending the picture-taking session were Bronocs owner Pat
Bowlen, general manager John Beake, coach Dan Reeves and defensive
safety Dennis Smith.
   With Elway sitting out the game because of an attack of stomach
flu, the Broncos defeated the Washington Redskins 14-10 Monday
night in Washington.
