<SECOND>PM-SoCal Earthquake,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Small Earthquake Rattles Parts of Riverside County</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIVERSIDE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small earthquake rattled parts of
this Southern California city, but no injuries or damage were
reported.
   The quake measuring 2.9 on the Richter scale struck at 10:48
a.m. Monday and was centered 17 miles south of Riverside, said Hall
Daily, a spokesman for the California Institute of Technology.
   ``It was very small,'' said Daily. ``We only got a few calls
about it,''
   Riverside is about 50 miles east of Los Angeles.
   The open-ended Richter scale is a gauge of the energy released
by an earthquake, as measured by the ground motion recorded on a
seismograph. An earthquake of 3.5 on the Richter scale can cause
slight damage in the local area.
