<HEAD>Poo Poo Choo-Choo is Back</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BALTIMORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A train dubbed the ``poo poo choo-choo'' for
its cargo of sewage sludge is back from the South after failing to
find a place to unload.
   The city of Baltimore had contracted with GSX Chemical Services
of Columbia, S.C., to dispose of the cargo at a White Castle, La.,
waste treatment plant.
   However, officials in Louisiana said the waste was so smelly
that they would not allow it to be unloaded. Mississippi wouldn't
accept the cargo, either.
   GSX returned the 5,000 tons of sludge to Baltimore, where the
train is parked at a railyard while public works officials figure
out what to do next.
