<HEAD>Three Killed in Land Mine Blast in Southwest Sudan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KHARTOUM, Sudan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A land mine exploded in southwestern
Sudan, killing three policemen and injuring several others, the
Sudan News Agency said Tuesday.
   The police were accompanying a supply convoy from Kadugli to
Saififa on Sunday when the explosion occurred, the state-run news
agency said.
   The police had been sent to the area, about 375 miles southwest
of Khartoum, to prevent more tribal clashes that killed 68 people
last month.
   The agency did not say who planted the mine, but southern rebels
belonging to the Sudan People's Liberation Army are known to have
extended their activities into southwestern Sudan.
