<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--China-Execution     11-21 0105</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Execution,0108</SECOND>
<HEAD>Policewoman Executed For Taking Bribes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A policewoman was executed in southern China on
Tuesday for taking bribes to find rural residents places to live in
the city, the official Xinhua News Agency reported.
   Zhang Mayun, who supervised household registrations, was
executed with an accomplice, saleswoman Chen Heilian, in the city
of Canton, Xinhua said.
   Ms. Zhang took the equivalent of $76,000 in bribes to transfer
63 people from rural areas into the city, Xinhua said.
   The two were arrested in June 1988 and sentenced to death a year
later, the report said. Their appeals were turned down, Xinhua said.
