<HEAD>Francestown Residents Raise Money to Help Crime Victims</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANCESTOWN, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Residents of this small town have shown
that it's never too early for the Christmas spirit of giving.
   Townspeople passed the hat last week and raised $837 for Kim and
Kip Dalley, owners of the Francestown Village Store, who were
robbed of $701 on Nov. 11.
   ``There are a lot of people that (Kip) did a lot of things for
in town,'' said Bob Podsadowski, who came up with the idea. ``I had
to do something.''
   More than 100 people signed a card and donated money.
