<HEAD>Millionaire's Widow Gets Life For Husband's Slaying</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A millionaire's widow was sentenced to life in
prison today for hiring three men to kill her husband for $100,000.
   Joyce Cohen, 39, was spared the electric chair when Circuit
Judge Fredricka Smith backed a jury's recommendation of a life
term. Under law, she cannot be paroled for 25 years.
   Prosecutors claimed the Cohens' 11-year marriage had soured and
Mrs. Cohen feared a divorce would end her jet-set lifestyle.
Defense attorneys tried to blame the slaying of 52-year-old Stanley
Cohen on his purported drug connections.
   Prosecutors said Mrs. Cohen hired three men to kill her husband,
supplied a map of their Coconut Grove home, disconnected the
alarms, unlocked the door and gave them her husband's gun. Cohen
was shot in the head four times at their home in 1986.
