<HEAD>Reagan Postpones Appearance in Sympathy with Jesuits</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former President Ronald Reagan postponed a
visit Tuesday to Loyola Marymount University in sympathy with the
Jesuit community, which is mourning the killing of six priests in
El Salvador.
   ``Because of the tragedy which has befallen the Jesuit
community, President Reagan has decided to postpone his visit,''
said Mark Weinberg, his spokesman.
   Several students and people living off campus called
Jesuit-operated Loyola Marymount to protest Reagan's visit in light
of the massacre, according to David Herbst, a student and chairman
of the speakers program.
