contributing to the slayings Thursday, said Herbst.
   The six priests, their housekeeper and her daughter were shot to
death at their home behind the Catholic university in San Salvador.
Men wearing military uniforms were spotted entering the university
before the slaying.
   Melaney Nunez, Loyola's student body president, said the campus
was looking forward to Reagan's rescheduled visit, probably in late
January. The visit was sponsored by the students, their Republican
and Democratic clubs and the political science department, Herbst
said.
