<FIRST>r a AM-People-Bridges     11-21 0311</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Bridges,0319</SECOND>
<HEAD>Prosecutor Refiles Felony Assault Charge Against `Diff'rent Strokes'
Star</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A felony assault charge was refiled Tuesday
against former child television star Todd Bridges, who was
acquitted by a jury earlier this month of more serious charges in
the shooting of a drug dealer.
   Bridges, who faces up to six years in prison if convicted,
pleaded innocent to assault with a firearm and remained free on
$25,000 bail pending a Jan. 25 hearing, said Mike Botula of the
district attorney's office.
   Jurors found Bridges innocent Nov. 7 of attempted murder and the
lesser charge of attempted voluntary manslaughter. Two days later,
the panel announced it was deadlocked 8-4 in favor of acquitting
him on a charge of assault with a deadly weapon.
   The former member of the cast of the series ``Diff'rent
Strokes'' was originally charged with shooting eight bullets into
Kenneth ``Tex'' Clay and slashing his throat during a Feb. 2
scuffle in a south-central Los Angeles ``crack'' house where
cocaine was being peddled.
   Clay, 25, survived the attack and testified Bridges was ``based
out'' from freebasing or smoking cocaine when the shooting
occurred. ``He looked like his eyes were about to jump out of his
head,'' Clay said.
   Clay described himself as a bodyguard for the owner of the house
where Bridges was living and said Bridges was taking weapons from
the house and selling them.
   Defense attorney Johnnie L. Cochran Jr. maintained throughout
the trial that Bridges shot Clay in self-defense.
   Bridges, 24, who for eight years played actor Gary Coleman's
brother Willis on ``Diff'rent Strokes,'' testified he became
depressed and turned to drugs after the situation comedy was
canceled in 1986.
   On Nov. 13, Harvie Eugene Duckett, 31, who testified that he
helped Bridges attack Clay, was placed on three years' probation as
part of a plea bargain agreement with prosecutors.
</TEXT>
