<SECOND>AM-Bush-Family Week,90</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bush Proclaims `National Family Week'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush signed a proclamation Tuesday
declaring this National Family Week.
   ``The integrity of the family is essential to our ability to
remain a strong and stable nation,'' the president said. ``During
National Family Week, we renew our determination to strengthen and
support the American family.''
   In addition to proclaiming this week of Nov. 19-25 National
Family Week, Bush made the same designation for Nov. 18-24, 1990.
   Earlier, he signed a separate proclamation declaring Nov. 20-26
National Adoption Week.
</TEXT>
