<FILEID>AP-NR-11-21-89 2006EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u i AM-Israel     11-21 0371</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Israel,0385</SECOND>
<HEAD>Israelis Riot Following Death of Girl Struck by Truck</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dozens of enraged Israelis blocked a Jerusalem
street with garbage cans and burning bushes Tuesday to protest the
death of a Jewish girl struck by a garbage truck driven by an Arab.
   ``Death to the Arabs!'' shouted the rioters in the Shmuel Hanavi
district in northern Jerusalem.
   Police said the 7-year-old girl was killed instantly when she
was hit by the truck driven by a city employee.
   ``The driver was an Arab. .... Somebody saw him going wild on
the road, and others say he pulled the girl and ran over her,
shouting `Allahu Akbar' (God is Great),'' a man from Shmuel Hanavi
told Israel radio. He was not identified.
   City police chief Arye Bibi told reporters, ``The driver indeed
was an Arab, but it had nothing to do with the accident. The driver
was arrested and his interrogation raised no possibility at all
that he did it for political reasons.
   ``He works for the municipality, he was driving here and hit the
girl.''
   Israel radio quoted police officials as saying the girl
apparently ran into the road from behind a parked bus and the truck
driver did not see her.
   Residents of Shmuel Hanavi, a working-class district, have held
street demonstrations in the past to protest Arab attacks on
Israelis in the 23-month-old Palestinian uprising. They stoned
Arab-owned vehicles, injuring some motoritsts, but the district has
been quiet in recent months.
   In the occupied West Bank and the Gaza Strip, Israeli soldiers
shot and wounded at least six Palestinians, Arab doctors said.
   The army command confirmed two wounded and said the victims were
in a ``suspicious looking car'' near the West Bank town of Jenin
and ignored orders by soldiers to stop.
   The troops shouted warnings and fired in the air before shooting
at the car, the army said. It did not identify the victims but said
they were wanted by security forces and were taken to an Israeli
hospital.
   Arab reporters identified the two as Ihsan Moani, 20, and Yusef
Al Heid, 20.
   At least 615 Palestinians have been killed by Israeli gunfire
during the uprising. The violence also has claimed 42 Israeli lives.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
