<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Sony     11-21 0188</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Sony,0199</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sony Posts 68 Rise In First-Half Profit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sony Corp.'s profit soared more than 68 percent in
the first half of fiscal 1989 amid booming sales overseas, the
company said Tuesday.
   Net income for Sony and its consolidated subsidiaries totaled
49.062 billion yen, or about $340 million using Tuesday's
dollar-yen exchange rate, up from 29.183 billion yen a year earlier.
   Sales rose to 1.229 trillion yen, up 23.8 percent from 992.260
billion yen in the comparable year-earlier period.
   Domestic sales continued to make up the largest part of Sony's
overall sales in the six months. But despite booming personal
spending in Japan, Sony marked up its strongest sales gains
overseas, particularly in Europe.
   European sales jumped 30.3 percent to 285.381 billion yen from
218.962 billion yen a year earlier.
   Sales in the United States climbed 26.5 percent to 365.140
billion yen from 281.586 billion yen, while sales inside Japan
increased a more moderate 16 percent to 390.911 billion yen from
336.973 billion yen.
   Sales of recordings by Sony's subsidiary CBS Records Inc. rose
18.8 percent to 192.838 billion yen from 162.382 billion yen.
</TEXT>
