   The stock market was higher in early trading
today.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 5.97 points at
2,638.01 at 10 am EST after a half-hour of trading.
   Volume on the Big Board totaled 19.96 million shares.
   The market appeared to be unperturbed by a government report
today on inflation that was slightly worse than most analysts had
been expecting.
   The Labor Department reported that consumer prices shot up 0.5
