<SECOND>PM-Avon-Bass,0380</SECOND>
<HEAD>Group Headed By Bass Acquires 5.9 Percent Stake in Avon</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN M. DOYLE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An investment group headed by Texas financier
Robert M. Bass said today it has acquired a 5.9 percent stake in
the cosmetics company Avon Products Inc.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, Bass
said the group had purchased a total of 2.5 million shares between
Oct. 3 and last Friday for prices ranging between $27.35 and $36.80
a share.
   The filing said the shares were purchased ``for investment
purposes,'' but it added the group may have discussions in the
future with Avon management ``concerning the issuers's recent
operating history as well as the issuer's general business outlook
and prospects.''
   The filing said the group also may ``engage in discussions with
other persons, including other shareholders'' of Avon.
   Last week, Avon sought to repel unwanted takeover advances from
an alliance of powerful investors including oil heir Gordon P.
Getty, a senior Mary Kay Corp. executive and the Fisher real estate
family of New York.
   A limited partnership called Chartwell Associates, revealing its
intentions after it became known Friday that the group had bought a
stake in Avon, said it may propose a merger with Avon or one of its
affiliates.
   In a summary of a document filed with the SEC, Chartwell
Associates LP disclosed that it owns 6.9 percent of Avon's common
stock and intends to purchase additional shares.
   Earlier this year Avon rejected outright takeover proposals from
the rival direct sales company Amway Corp. of Ada, Mich., and from
Minneapolis-based investor Irwin Jacobs.
   Avon also fended off takeover feelers from Mary Kay. Amway
offered $2.1 billion for Avon and Jacobs' offer was worth $2.85
billion.
   In addition to Bass, of Fort Worth, Texas, and the Robert M.
Bass Group Inc., the other purchasers of Avon shares listed in the
SEC filing were:
   Texas Partners Ltd.; John H. Scully and William E. Oberndorf,
both of Mill Valley. Calif.;TexGenPar, a Texas limited partnership;
The Bonderman Family Limited Partnership, a Texas securities
limited partnership; David Bonderman, of Fort Worth, Texas; San
Francisco Partners II, a California securities limited partnership;
and William J. Patterson.
</TEXT>
