<HEAD>London Shares End Slightly Higher</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES with close</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   London share prices ended slightly higher Tuesday
as stocks rebounded despite bearish signals from the futures market.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index ended 2
points, or 0.09 percent, higher at 2,185.1 points, its session
high. The index's low was 2,171.0 points.
   Volume came to 350.6 million shares, compared with 364.9 million
shares on Monday.
   The rise was achieved despite downward signals from the FT-SE
100 futures contract, which closed at a 14-point discount to the
underlying market. Normally, the futures contract shows a
3-to-5-point premium.
   The market started lower as the pound came under pressure on the
foreign exchange market.
   But the stronger pound in the afternoon, combined with a healthy
opening on Wall Street, helped the London market move into positive
territory.
