<FIRST>d f BC-MayStock     11-21 0179</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-May Stock,0185</SECOND>
<HEAD>May Department Stores In Stock Buy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   May Department Stores Co. said Tuesday it had
agreed to purchase more than 14 million shares of its common stock
from May Centers Associates for $663 million.
   May spokesman Jim Abrams said the agreement also calls for the
purchase by May Centers and leaseback to May of department store
properties owned by May and valued at $585 million.
   Abrams said the transactions are expected to close in January,
subject to approval by the boards of directors of May and each of
the corporate partners of May Centers, Prudential Insurance Co. of
America and Melvin Simon &amp; Associates (PruSimon). May and PruSimon
equally own May Centers.
   May Centers was formed in August 1988 as a real estate-oriented
shopping center development partnership. PruSimon contributed cash
to the partnership and May contributed the stock it has now agreed
to repurchase.
   ``The net effect of the transaction is to raise earnings per
share of May shareholders and put a real estate investment more
appropriately in the partnership,'' said Abrams.
</TEXT>
