<TEXT>
   Robert Levine, managing director of the San
Francisco office of Laventhol &amp; Horwath, will become the accounting
firm's next chief executive officer in June, the company announced
Tuesday.
   Levin succeeds George Bernstein, whose second five-year term
expires this year.
