<FIRST>r f BC-SouthKorea-Trade     11-21 0131</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-South Korea-Trade,0136</SECOND>
<HEAD>Korean Trade Surpluses With U.S., EEC Decrease Sharply</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   South Korea's trade surplus with the
United States from January to October fell to $3.76 billion, a 44.4
percent drop compared with the same period last year, the Korea
Foreign Trade Association reported Wednesday.
   South Korean exports to the United States in the first 10 months
of this year dropped 1.8 percent from a year ago to $16.8 billion,
while imports from America jumped 26.2 percent to $13.04 billion,
according to the association.
   Korea's trade surplus with the European Economic Community
during the period dropped 60 percent to $680 million.
   Korea's trade deficit with Japan during the 10 months stood at
$3.27 billion, up 0.5 percent or $17 million from a year ago.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
